02:30.494 --> 02:32.244
[sirens wailing]

02:32.296 --> 02:36.215
♪<i> Oh, calcium mines you
buried deep in your chest</i> ♪

02:36.250 --> 02:37.800
[man] <i> Drop the weapon!
Let's see your hands!</i>

02:37.835 --> 02:39.752
<i>Drop the weapon now!</i>

02:39.804 --> 02:41.170
Go!

02:41.222 --> 02:43.489
♪<i> You're deep in a mine</i> ♪

02:43.524 --> 02:44.523
[grunts]

02:44.559 --> 02:49.261
[cellphone vibrates]

02:49.286 --> 02:50.610
Yeah.

02:52.892 --> 02:54.219
Okay. Where?

02:56.520 --> 02:58.304
I'm coming.

03:12.520 --> 03:16.655
[car doors close]

03:18.225 --> 03:19.992
How you keeping?

03:20.027 --> 03:22.595
[indistinct conversations]

03:26.033 --> 03:27.700
[man] I appreciate this.

03:31.222 --> 03:32.282
[car door closes]

03:33.140 --> 03:34.974
[car door opens]

03:43.868 --> 03:44.727
Okay.

03:45.403 --> 03:48.070
You got something in your stomach now.

03:48.122 --> 03:49.655
The cops are far away.

03:49.657 --> 03:51.991
This is when you tell me
what the fuck transpired

03:51.993 --> 03:52.782
inside that head of yours.

03:53.294 --> 03:55.274
I was blowing steam, I guess.

03:56.907 --> 03:58.998
You're not tanking anymore.

03:59.050 --> 04:02.063
I've seen your runs.
You pulled past even.

04:02.420 --> 04:03.836
Open road ahead of you.

04:03.838 --> 04:06.571
It was an $8 million day to the good.

04:07.975 --> 04:09.341
[sighs]

04:09.343 --> 04:11.711
I had a drink. Three.

04:12.596 --> 04:14.024
Watched the Yanks lose.

04:15.766 --> 04:19.284
And then there was just... nothing.

04:19.320 --> 04:20.853
You don't feel anything.

04:20.855 --> 04:23.188
Maybe a twinge when I get crushed.

04:23.190 --> 04:24.523
Nothing when I'm up.

04:24.525 --> 04:25.399
[Bobby] It happens.

04:25.960 --> 04:28.527
You ever do this thing where
you pull up your positions

04:28.562 --> 04:30.396
and just stare at them on the screen?

04:30.431 --> 04:33.198
Try to really hold on to
all that money inside?

04:33.234 --> 04:35.034
No.

04:35.086 --> 04:36.802
Does it make you feel happy when you do?

04:36.837 --> 04:38.704
Like it's enough?

04:38.739 --> 04:39.738
No.

04:39.774 --> 04:41.040
Right.

04:41.092 --> 04:43.509
Because what drives you
doesn't understand "enough."

04:45.429 --> 04:48.485
Well, last night, I was doing it...
Staring at the numbers.

04:49.550 --> 04:51.860
I look away from the
screen, out the window,

04:52.219 --> 04:53.500
and I see them out there,

04:54.722 --> 04:56.805
eating everything we planted

04:57.641 --> 04:59.789
like it's a fucking salad bar for them.

05:01.219 --> 05:03.946
And then just... rage

05:05.066 --> 05:06.953
over how fucking stupid they are.

05:08.069 --> 05:11.070
Eat, move, shit. Eat, move, shit. Repeat.

05:11.122 --> 05:13.238
I mean, how can things
that dumb have the gall

05:13.274 --> 05:15.457
to occupy the same space that I do?

05:15.493 --> 05:17.176
Does that one make any sense to you?

05:18.279 --> 05:19.555
Yeah, more than you know.

05:24.351 --> 05:25.834
Is that Pete Decker?

05:25.886 --> 05:26.752
[Chuck] What?

05:27.610 --> 05:29.188
He used to work at Axe.

05:29.423 --> 05:31.323
Do you have business with him?

05:31.358 --> 05:32.424
Which guy?

05:32.476 --> 05:33.592
Decker. There.

05:36.013 --> 05:37.429
I don't know. I guess I missed him.

05:37.431 --> 05:38.931
- I love you.
- [smooches]

05:38.933 --> 05:40.632
Talk to you, okay?

05:41.986 --> 05:45.321
Look, there won't be any
record of what happened here.

05:46.357 --> 05:47.673
It's been worked out.

05:49.282 --> 05:50.509
But I'll remember.

05:51.495 --> 05:52.845
I can't have this.

05:54.094 --> 05:56.477
[Bobby] Can't give the world
another reason to hate us.

05:56.917 --> 05:59.852
Can't give a wedge to law
enforcement, a way in.

06:01.205 --> 06:02.254
You understand?

06:04.447 --> 06:06.458
Go get yourself coffee.
Shower in the gym.

06:06.510 --> 06:09.044
Don't fucking talk about
any of this to anyone.

06:10.297 --> 06:13.465
Keep it together. All right?

06:16.020 --> 06:18.303
[Pete] <i> What you need to
know before we even start</i>

06:18.355 --> 06:20.038
is how tight these guys
are with each other.

06:20.074 --> 06:22.207
[Pete] They are grateful,
and they're scared.

06:22.243 --> 06:24.576
[Chuck] Let's get started.

06:24.612 --> 06:25.611
This is a proffer session,

06:25.646 --> 06:26.745
otherwise known as Queen for a Day.

06:26.781 --> 06:27.846
[sighs]

06:27.882 --> 06:30.149
[Bryan] As the documents
you signed state,

06:30.201 --> 06:31.316
you lay out everything illegal

06:31.318 --> 06:32.718
you've done in the securities industry,

06:32.753 --> 06:34.853
particularly in regards to Axe Capital,

06:34.889 --> 06:38.157
in return for a felony 5K
letter-reducing sentence.

06:38.209 --> 06:40.793
If you are untruthful or withholding,

06:40.828 --> 06:42.761
you can and will be prosecuted.

06:42.797 --> 06:44.797
[sighs]

06:48.719 --> 06:51.657
"Sing for your supper and you'll
get breakfast in the morn'."

06:54.308 --> 06:57.843
But what they don't spell out
in that, uh, fine show stopper

06:57.845 --> 07:01.246
is what happens when you decide
that you forgot the tune.

07:02.683 --> 07:06.485
Well, then you go to jail,
Pete, and so do mom and dad.

07:08.422 --> 07:11.023
So, is it prison or start talking?

07:13.194 --> 07:15.508
Just another schnook
running his own money.

07:16.363 --> 07:18.594
Fucking egg noodles with ketchup.

07:20.634 --> 07:23.602
Okay. Let's do this.

07:23.838 --> 07:26.705
How does the day start at Axe Capital?

07:26.707 --> 07:28.207
What does Axe do?

07:28.209 --> 07:30.676
The real answer is anything he wants.

07:31.679 --> 07:33.045
[Pete] When you're at his level,

07:33.097 --> 07:35.597
you're more like a
nation-state than a person.

07:35.633 --> 07:37.966
There is no schedule he's following.

07:38.018 --> 07:39.768
<i>I mean, when he shows
up, the meeting starts.</i>

07:39.803 --> 07:41.553
[Chuck] <i> I got it. He's rich.</i> Let's go.

07:41.605 --> 07:42.554
[Pete] <i> Rich?</i>

07:42.606 --> 07:43.889
<i>Rich is a Marquis Jet card,</i>

07:43.941 --> 07:45.774
<i>uh, flying out East on a chopper.</i>

07:45.809 --> 07:48.227
<i>This is more like, "Hey,
I want a cheesesteak.</i>

07:48.229 --> 07:49.461
<i>Send some guy to Philly</i>

07:49.496 --> 07:50.729
<i>and bring them back for everyone."</i>

07:50.781 --> 07:51.886
Jim's or Shank's?

07:51.972 --> 07:54.006
[Pete] <i> Both. And Tony Luke's.</i>

07:54.235 --> 07:57.486
<i>The fact is, he does not
need to call meetings.</i>

07:57.538 --> 07:59.621
<i>Everywhere he goes, they form around him.</i>

07:59.657 --> 08:02.241
<i>I mean, he's like a...
Like an aircraft carrier</i>

08:02.243 --> 08:03.625
<i>in the center of a strike group.</i>

08:03.661 --> 08:04.743
<i>When he turns left,</i>

08:04.745 --> 08:06.478
battleships, destroyers, subs,

08:06.513 --> 08:08.247
they all turn left with him.

08:08.299 --> 08:09.298
- I could use a coffee.
- Yeah.

08:09.333 --> 08:11.250
- Anyone else?
- In a minute.

08:11.252 --> 08:12.417
Keep going.

08:12.469 --> 08:13.635
[sighs]

08:13.671 --> 08:15.087
You just don't know where
his focus is gonna stand.

08:15.139 --> 08:16.755
Sometimes, you hope it lands on you.

08:16.807 --> 08:18.557
Sometimes, you wish you were invisible.

08:18.592 --> 08:22.427
Because when it does land
on you, he sees everything.

08:22.479 --> 08:24.196
[Mafee] No, no.

08:24.231 --> 08:26.798
I did get the offer, but
I did turn it down.

08:26.834 --> 08:28.350
That's what I was coming to tell you.

08:28.402 --> 08:29.601
Good.

08:29.603 --> 08:31.103
Because it seemed like maybe
you were trying to tell me

08:31.155 --> 08:33.105
if I didn't match it,
you were gonna leave.

08:33.107 --> 08:35.340
No, I was... trying to be loyal.

08:35.376 --> 08:37.859
You don't try to be loyal. You just are.

08:37.912 --> 08:38.876
Or you're not.

08:38.913 --> 08:40.607
I am.

08:41.582 --> 08:43.782
Well, that's heartening, Mafee.

08:43.784 --> 08:46.518
[sighs]

08:46.553 --> 08:47.819
Information flow.

08:47.855 --> 08:49.621
When you are Bobby Axelrod,

08:49.673 --> 08:51.506
you don't chase information.

08:51.542 --> 08:53.292
Information flows to you.

08:53.294 --> 08:55.727
- What kind?
- [Pete] All kinds.

08:55.763 --> 08:57.796
It could be an owner of a sports team

08:57.798 --> 08:59.464
inviting him to sit in a box

08:59.466 --> 09:00.899
at a... at an all-star game

09:00.935 --> 09:02.801
or some leader of an African republic

09:02.803 --> 09:04.412
looking for a-a handout.

09:04.905 --> 09:07.306
While the rest of us are
plugging away, ants,

09:07.358 --> 09:08.740
he sees the whole board.

09:09.764 --> 09:10.530
Hey.

09:10.811 --> 09:12.377
[Constantine] <i> You always
said to call this number,</i>

09:12.413 --> 09:15.213
and only this number, in a
circumstance like this.

09:18.319 --> 09:19.404
[Bobby] <i>I understand.</i>

09:20.871 --> 09:22.764
This has to be an in-person conversation.

09:23.657 --> 09:25.240
[Bobby] <i> I'll tell you a time and place.</i>

09:26.210 --> 09:28.060
<i>Hey, and thanks for the
call, Constantine.</i>

09:28.095 --> 09:29.350
You're a good friend.

09:29.997 --> 09:31.997
[Pete] <i> You never really know
what he's doing or why.</i>

09:32.639 --> 09:33.665
<i>I mean, he says he's going to Morocco</i>

09:33.667 --> 09:35.100
<i>to check out a seven-star hotel,</i>

09:35.135 --> 09:37.085
<i>but then you find out
he's really in Hangzhou</i>

09:37.137 --> 09:38.170
<i>making a web-portal play.</i>

09:38.222 --> 09:39.721
Oh, hey. Pouch needs a minute with you.

09:39.757 --> 09:40.973
Later.

09:41.008 --> 09:43.592
Metallica's playing one North
American gig this year.

09:43.644 --> 09:44.743
Tonight. Quebec.

09:44.778 --> 09:45.944
We going?

09:45.980 --> 09:47.980
You're half right. You
got the conn, brother.

09:48.015 --> 09:49.247
And like I always say...

09:49.283 --> 09:51.600
Don't fuck it up. I know.

09:51.652 --> 09:53.652
♪<i> funky music plays</i> ♪

09:57.941 --> 09:59.658
- There he is!
- [Bobby] Hey!

09:59.693 --> 10:00.692
There he is!

10:01.695 --> 10:02.761
[car door closes]

10:02.796 --> 10:04.296
Kill 'em all, baby!

10:04.331 --> 10:05.864
- Whoo-hoo!
- [Ike] Yeah, kill 'em all!

10:05.916 --> 10:07.366
- Axe!
- [laughs]

10:07.418 --> 10:10.035
Fuck, fellas. It is good to see you.

10:10.087 --> 10:11.953
- How are you, bro?
- Metallica? Holy shit.

10:12.006 --> 10:13.672
I couldn't be more psyched if you told me

10:13.707 --> 10:16.041
Jillian Barberie was gonna ride
my face like American Pharoah.

10:16.093 --> 10:17.626
That's beautiful. I want
that on my tombstone.

10:17.678 --> 10:18.543
All yours.

10:18.595 --> 10:19.878
Hey, where's Freddy? Not coming?

10:19.930 --> 10:21.046
Yeah, he's late, as usual.

10:21.048 --> 10:22.764
Yeah, you know what? We
should leave his ass.

10:22.800 --> 10:24.383
Rule is if a guy is flying you somewhere,

10:24.435 --> 10:26.351
he gets to show up last,
step on the plane,

10:26.387 --> 10:27.853
close the door, take off, right?

10:27.888 --> 10:29.821
If you own the plane, you don't wait.

10:29.857 --> 10:31.189
That's the rules, but not for you guys.

10:31.225 --> 10:33.358
Never for you guys. Come on.

10:35.562 --> 10:37.729
Ah, that's not Freddy. Shit.

10:40.784 --> 10:41.900
Dude.

10:41.902 --> 10:43.735
How far do I have to
go not to be bothered?

10:43.737 --> 10:44.836
I wanted to catch you...

10:44.872 --> 10:46.471
- Sorry I'm late, man.
- [Ike] Freddy!

10:46.507 --> 10:47.989
Freddy! Hey, what's up, brother?

10:48.042 --> 10:49.574
- Hey.
- Hey, jump on. Jump on.

10:49.576 --> 10:51.243
- I'll be there in a sec.
- Okay.

10:51.245 --> 10:54.012
Have to talk about the Cross-Co. short.

10:54.048 --> 10:55.247
[Butch] I didn't understand the play

10:55.299 --> 10:56.415
when you had me make it.

10:56.467 --> 10:57.466
Now I do.

10:57.501 --> 10:58.917
We should get out of the position.

10:58.969 --> 11:00.419
I'd never do that.

11:00.471 --> 11:02.421
It's the only way to eliminate
potential conflict of interest.

11:02.423 --> 11:04.723
- [Bobby] There's no conflict.
- [Butch] Come on.

11:04.758 --> 11:06.091
It won't look good.

11:06.143 --> 11:07.926
You set the position then jump
onto the board of YumTime.

11:07.978 --> 11:09.594
[Bobby] If I made moves...

11:09.596 --> 11:11.430
- [camera shutter clicks]
- ...based on what looked good,

11:11.432 --> 11:13.231
I'm damn sure I wouldn't
have this puppy right here.

11:13.267 --> 11:14.516
And I'm on lots of boards.

11:14.568 --> 11:15.817
[car door closes]

11:15.853 --> 11:17.235
Those don't have contracts
they're dumping

11:17.271 --> 11:18.837
with Cross-Co. Trucking.

11:21.442 --> 11:23.108
- [car door closes]
- A guy I talked to

11:23.160 --> 11:24.443
who traffics in the name

11:24.445 --> 11:26.027
says he's hearing whispers

11:26.080 --> 11:27.546
the contract's going to be cancelled.

11:27.581 --> 11:29.614
This opens us up to contract steering,

11:29.666 --> 11:30.949
manipulation.

11:30.951 --> 11:31.959
It opens me up.

11:32.453 --> 11:35.387
I didn't have the board seat
when we took the short position.

11:35.422 --> 11:38.056
And I don't have anything to do
with the day-to-day at YumTime

11:38.092 --> 11:39.458
or their contracts with vendors.

11:39.460 --> 11:41.793
There's no paper that says I do.

11:41.845 --> 11:44.713
So, the only thing you're
open to is making some money,

11:44.765 --> 11:46.565
which would make a nice change.

11:46.600 --> 11:47.716
[Freddy chuckles]

11:47.768 --> 11:49.885
Like your wife says, hold
the fucking position

11:49.937 --> 11:51.803
until I tell you I'm done.

11:51.805 --> 11:53.772
[laughter] Come on. Come on.

11:53.807 --> 11:54.890
I guess that meeting's over, huh?

11:54.942 --> 11:56.191
Shotgun!

11:56.226 --> 11:57.476
All right.

11:58.365 --> 12:00.729
Inside information, specifically.

12:00.781 --> 12:02.314
Where is it coming from?

12:02.316 --> 12:03.381
[sighs]

12:03.417 --> 12:05.150
Where does rain come from?

12:05.202 --> 12:07.152
The sky. God himself.

12:07.204 --> 12:12.157
[chuckles] Information comes
from everywhere and all at once,

12:12.209 --> 12:13.892
from guys who owe him,

12:13.927 --> 12:17.546
guys he's worked, charmed,
hired, paid off for years.

12:17.581 --> 12:20.465
Sell-side traders looking to get
a gold star next to their name.

12:20.501 --> 12:21.583
Disgruntled employees,

12:21.635 --> 12:23.335
execs at the company in question,

12:23.337 --> 12:25.837
an analyst covering a stock
who feels underpaid.

12:25.839 --> 12:27.839
Like rain, it comes.

12:27.891 --> 12:30.175
Sounds like it's great to be Axe.

12:30.177 --> 12:33.178
It is. But it's a zero-sum game.

12:33.230 --> 12:35.096
Kill and eat or be eaten.

12:35.149 --> 12:36.481
I mean, don't kid yourselves.

12:36.517 --> 12:37.732
These guys are like kings.

12:37.768 --> 12:40.318
Someone is always coming
to assassinate them.

12:44.775 --> 12:46.191
You ready, Quince?

12:46.193 --> 12:47.359
[Quince] Yeah.

12:47.361 --> 12:49.277
But you're gonna love what I just heard

12:49.329 --> 12:51.263
from this British fruit, Farraday,

12:51.298 --> 12:53.098
my guy on the stock loan desk.

12:53.133 --> 12:55.167
Guess which hedge-funder's got himself

12:55.202 --> 12:56.952
in a precarious short,

12:57.004 --> 12:58.537
ripe for a squeeze?

12:58.539 --> 13:00.422
If you're talking Bobby Axelrod,

13:00.457 --> 13:03.708
this just became my
favorite round of the year.

13:03.760 --> 13:06.211
- [Chuck Sr.] You have details?
- I do.

13:06.213 --> 13:09.881
Hit first. And talk.

13:09.883 --> 13:13.318
I want to know what stock
I'm running up his ass.

13:13.353 --> 13:17.889
It's a trucking company... Cross-Co.

13:19.226 --> 13:21.459
Right here on the course?

13:21.495 --> 13:23.862
I'm President Emeritus.

13:23.897 --> 13:26.231
I do what I want.

13:26.233 --> 13:27.232
[chuckling]

13:27.284 --> 13:29.568
All right. To me.

13:31.038 --> 13:32.003
[Bobby] Come on.

13:32.039 --> 13:32.904
Eat those.

13:32.906 --> 13:34.372
