41:36.356 --> 41:39.140
[Pete] <i> Because you can't
know, not really.</i>

41:39.192 --> 41:41.526
<i>That's why even though I
opened up my own place,</i>

41:41.561 --> 41:44.812
<i>I could never have really
done it, been him.</i>

41:44.864 --> 41:46.230
<i>There's so much you have
to keep in your head...</i>

41:46.282 --> 41:48.616
<i>Balancing, weighing, deciding.</i>

41:48.651 --> 41:51.052
<i>You can't let anyone know
all of it, maybe any of it.</i>

41:51.087 --> 41:53.154
I mean, to be Bobby Axelrod

41:53.206 --> 41:56.324
is to keep so much in your head,

41:56.376 --> 41:58.543
just to keep it from
blowing up your brain

41:58.578 --> 42:01.496
takes Benedictine-monk-like discipline.

42:01.498 --> 42:04.999
Not sure the Benedictines
would dig the comparison.

42:06.336 --> 42:07.802
[Chuck] We're done.

42:12.759 --> 42:14.258
[door closes]

42:14.310 --> 42:16.344
Well, we didn't get what we
wanted, but we got something.

42:16.346 --> 42:18.679
Bill Stearn. Get the FBI on him now.

42:18.681 --> 42:21.933
I want this motherfucker's genome mapped.

42:21.985 --> 42:24.569
That is how deep I want this to go.

42:24.604 --> 42:26.604
Find out how he got what he got on Pepsum

42:26.656 --> 42:28.906
and whatever else dirty
he may do in this life.

42:28.942 --> 42:30.525
I want to put him on the rack

42:30.527 --> 42:34.128
and stretch him until he gives us Axe.

42:34.163 --> 42:36.797
Constantine, my old friend.

42:36.833 --> 42:39.367
- You showed.
- Of course.

42:39.369 --> 42:40.868
You said it was important,

42:40.870 --> 42:43.170
but I knew that meant total disaster.

42:44.591 --> 42:45.840
[sighs]

42:45.875 --> 42:48.109
I have been at Mundia
Tel my entire career.

42:48.144 --> 42:50.545
What people thought was
bedrock was really bullshit.

42:50.597 --> 42:53.581
But now everyone is going
to finally see the truth.

42:55.852 --> 42:57.418
I sensed that you, of all people,

42:57.453 --> 42:58.786
would understand...

42:58.821 --> 43:02.790
and would know what to do with
what I'm going to tell you.

43:02.825 --> 43:05.259
So tell me.

43:05.295 --> 43:07.461
♪<i> mid-tempo music plays</i> ♪

43:12.285 --> 43:14.135
[Bobby] Hey. Hey.

43:14.170 --> 43:16.270
Where are the guys?

43:16.306 --> 43:18.789
Uh... after party with the band.

43:18.825 --> 43:21.242
[chuckles]

43:21.294 --> 43:23.244
Oh, I picked that up for you.

43:23.296 --> 43:24.912
Thought you'd like it.

43:24.914 --> 43:26.948
Yeah, nice. Thanks.

43:30.587 --> 43:32.136
Thanks, man.

43:33.423 --> 43:35.923
What the fuck's wrong?

43:35.925 --> 43:38.259
I'm in some shit.

43:38.311 --> 43:40.177
I fucked up.

43:40.229 --> 43:41.996
Yeah? Fucked up how?

43:44.267 --> 43:47.318
Um...

43:47.353 --> 43:51.372
I heard your Cross-Co.
play on the runway,

43:51.407 --> 43:53.107
and I-I-I jumped on it.

43:53.142 --> 43:54.675
You rode along on my intel?

43:54.711 --> 43:56.844
I piggybacked because I
figured you always know.

43:56.879 --> 43:59.046
You stole my fucking idea.

43:59.082 --> 44:00.348
You're like Paulie Pennino.

44:00.383 --> 44:01.282
Who?

44:01.317 --> 44:02.984
Paulie, Adrian's brother,

44:03.019 --> 44:06.220
putting the Shamrock Meats
logo on Rocky's robe.

44:08.324 --> 44:12.059
You should've asked, man,
like any friend would.

44:12.095 --> 44:13.761
If you had, we could have worked it out

44:13.796 --> 44:15.863
to get you in on this without
attracting attention.

44:15.898 --> 44:20.534
Instead, you... you promoted
me like someone at work.

44:20.561 --> 44:23.202
They don't get to be here. You do.

44:23.296 --> 44:26.140
I know. I-I know. I fucked up.

44:26.142 --> 44:29.310
I fucked up.

44:29.312 --> 44:33.314
I-I put pretty much
everything into that short.

44:33.316 --> 44:35.149
And then, when the stock took off,

44:35.151 --> 44:37.034
it was too late to ask you for help,

44:37.070 --> 44:40.788
and now I-I'm getting a margin call.

44:40.823 --> 44:42.490
Broker's saying I got to
make good by morning,

44:42.492 --> 44:43.724
but I can't cover.

44:43.760 --> 44:46.594
I'm ready to... I'm ready
to puke all over myself.

44:46.629 --> 44:47.762
How much?

44:47.797 --> 44:49.497
How much do I owe?

44:49.532 --> 44:50.631
Yeah.

44:50.667 --> 44:52.800
I want to know how much
our friendship's worth.

44:59.509 --> 45:01.842
I'm in the hole just a
little over $210,000.

45:01.844 --> 45:05.312
I'm gonna be pretty much wiped out.

45:14.691 --> 45:16.607
This your brokerage?

45:16.659 --> 45:18.275
Yeah.

45:20.413 --> 45:22.580
[sniffles]

45:28.037 --> 45:29.870
I'm sending instructions to my people

45:29.922 --> 45:32.707
to guarantee your margin.

45:33.710 --> 45:34.759
Axe, I...

45:34.794 --> 45:37.928
It'll turn around in the morning.

45:37.964 --> 45:39.714
Stay short.

45:39.716 --> 45:42.550
Don't cover until then.

45:42.552 --> 45:46.387
The thing you got to remember is
if a short's going against you,

45:46.422 --> 45:48.556
you got to be able to
withstand the pressure

45:48.591 --> 45:49.557
or it'll crush you.

45:49.592 --> 45:52.493
You see it all so clearly.

45:52.528 --> 45:54.395
I don't lie to myself,

45:54.430 --> 45:57.765
and I don't hold on to a loser.

45:57.800 --> 45:59.834
The moment it doesn't feel right,

45:59.869 --> 46:01.769
I let it go, get away from it.

46:04.340 --> 46:06.340
♪

46:09.545 --> 46:13.347
Let's call it a night.
Plane leaves at 9:30.

46:20.473 --> 46:22.556
Thanks, man.

46:35.605 --> 46:36.604
Hey.

46:36.606 --> 46:37.605
Hey.

46:37.657 --> 46:39.356
[Chuck] You know, I know you know.

46:39.408 --> 46:41.776
But, uh, that was Pete Decker today,

46:41.828 --> 46:43.611
and I'm proffering him.

46:43.663 --> 46:45.613
In that second, I felt, uh,

46:45.665 --> 46:47.531
guilty and defensive,

46:47.583 --> 46:50.668
so I dissembled.

46:50.703 --> 46:52.286
Oh, I put you in a position.

46:52.338 --> 46:53.287
I didn't mean to.

46:53.289 --> 46:55.706
But there were a hundred

46:55.758 --> 46:59.693
legitimate things you could have said,

46:59.729 --> 47:01.729
including, "I can't talk about it."

47:01.764 --> 47:03.798
You're right.

47:03.800 --> 47:06.350
Not to pile on, but your dad called me.

47:06.385 --> 47:07.902
Said he's been trying to
find you for the last hour.

47:07.937 --> 47:11.105
Yeah. He texted me six times.

47:11.140 --> 47:12.139
[chuckles]

47:12.141 --> 47:14.442
You know, he has a rare ability...

47:14.488 --> 47:16.605
It's a gift almost... To push my buttons.

47:16.630 --> 47:18.646
You know the plans he had for himself

47:18.698 --> 47:19.980
when he was your age,

47:20.032 --> 47:22.199
before the fire hit that building.

47:22.235 --> 47:25.319
When every paper in New
York calls you a slum lord,

47:25.371 --> 47:28.155
it doesn't help out a
brand-new political career.

47:28.157 --> 47:30.374
Now you're it.

47:30.409 --> 47:32.409
You're the chance to grow his own legend.

47:32.461 --> 47:35.246
If only you'd get into line
and do what he needs you to.

47:35.298 --> 47:37.832
And if you get chewed up in the process,

47:37.834 --> 47:39.900
well, hell, it was a good try.

47:39.936 --> 47:43.003
I just have to keep reminding
myself again and again and again

47:43.055 --> 47:46.974
that he can't help himself, you
know, when it comes to me.

47:47.009 --> 47:48.375
[Wendy] That's right.

47:50.229 --> 47:53.514
You know...

47:53.566 --> 47:56.684
you have to remember when it
comes to yourself, too...

47:56.686 --> 47:59.353
When you're raised by someone like that,

47:59.405 --> 48:03.157
your instincts, no matter
how hard you fight them,

48:03.192 --> 48:06.994
sometimes fall towards self-preservation.

48:07.029 --> 48:09.430
You end up hurting those you love, too.

48:12.201 --> 48:15.069
Yeah, I know.

48:15.104 --> 48:17.171
I'm trying.

48:19.175 --> 48:21.609
I know.

48:24.380 --> 48:26.380
♪<i> mellow music plays</i> ♪

48:30.052 --> 48:33.687
[line ringing]

48:34.480 --> 48:35.055
[Lara] <i> Hey.</i>

48:35.107 --> 48:36.774
[Bobby] I just wanted to see your face,

48:36.809 --> 48:38.309
hear your voice.

48:38.361 --> 48:40.060
<i>Here I am.</i>

48:41.752 --> 48:42.658
[Lara] <i> How was it?</i>

48:43.736 --> 48:45.682
Didn't turn out how I thought.

48:46.702 --> 48:48.485
This trip's given me a
lot to think about.

48:48.537 --> 48:49.737
It'll be good to get home.

48:49.789 --> 48:52.673
<i>It'll be good to have you home.</i>

48:52.708 --> 48:54.575
You want to go back to sleep?

48:54.610 --> 48:56.911
<i>No.</i>

48:56.963 --> 48:59.079
<i>I'll sit up with you for a bit.</i>

49:03.486 --> 49:05.135
[knock on door]

49:05.171 --> 49:08.672
[woman] Bonjour! Housekeeping!

49:08.724 --> 49:09.723
[knock on door]

49:09.759 --> 49:12.259
Hello? Monsieur?

49:12.261 --> 49:13.677
Service!

49:13.729 --> 49:15.763
[door opens]

49:25.191 --> 49:27.191
[keyboard clacking]

49:30.780 --> 49:33.213
[woman] <i> And in a near-term
crippling blow for Cross-Co.,</i>

49:33.249 --> 49:34.915
<i>its biggest and longest-running client,</i>

49:34.951 --> 49:36.333
<i>YumTime Bakeries,</i>

49:36.369 --> 49:38.552
<i>has announced it is dropping
the trucking company,</i>

49:38.587 --> 49:40.454
<i>citing rampant driver violations,</i>

49:40.489 --> 49:42.456
<i>even negligence as the cause.</i>

49:42.508 --> 49:43.791
Guys! Guys!

49:43.843 --> 49:44.959
[woman] <i> Analysts are
predicting a major dive</i>

49:44.961 --> 49:46.226
<i>for the mid-size shipper's stock...</i>

49:46.262 --> 49:47.628
Guys!

49:47.680 --> 49:49.463
Axe!

49:49.515 --> 49:51.849
Breakfast is on me!

49:55.571 --> 49:59.273
♪<i> Out on the streets,
that's where we'll meet</i> ♪

49:59.308 --> 50:03.360
♪<i> You make the night, I
always cross the line</i> ♪

50:03.396 --> 50:07.147
♪<i> Another day, some other way</i> ♪

50:07.149 --> 50:11.118
♪<i> We're gonna go, but then
we'll see you again</i> ♪

50:11.153 --> 50:13.520
♪<i> I've had enough, we've had enough...</i> ♪

50:13.556 --> 50:15.039
[Ike] Epic, man.

50:16.826 --> 50:18.375
That was an all-timer.

50:18.411 --> 50:20.961
♪<i> I knew right from the beginning ♪</i>

50:20.997 --> 50:22.396
Thanks for bringing us.

50:22.431 --> 50:25.065
Having you here made the trip, man.

50:25.101 --> 50:29.470
♪<i> I knew right from the start</i> ♪

50:29.505 --> 50:34.341
♪<i> You'd put an arrow through my heart</i> ♪

50:37.513 --> 50:39.580
♪<i> Round and round...</i> ♪

50:39.615 --> 50:41.982
[knock on door]

50:42.018 --> 50:45.853
♪<i> I'll tell you why...</i> ♪

50:45.855 --> 50:47.688
- [door slams]
- Well, I waited.

50:47.740 --> 50:49.289
You pumped the trucking-company stock.

50:49.325 --> 50:51.358
It's a bare-knuckles brawl.
I was just doing...

50:51.394 --> 50:53.027
Stop.

50:54.997 --> 50:58.699
Market manipulation,
insider trading, fraud.

50:58.734 --> 51:01.735
You bought it, and you propped it up.

51:02.805 --> 51:04.905
I'm just goddamn glad that
you haven't dumped it yet

51:04.940 --> 51:06.707
because then it would
be a slam-dunk case,

51:06.709 --> 51:08.175
and there would be absolutely nothing

51:08.210 --> 51:09.376
that I could do to help you.

51:09.378 --> 51:13.097
Even if my office chose not to prosecute,

51:13.132 --> 51:14.765
Eastern wouldn't.

51:14.800 --> 51:17.301
And as it is, I had to
give my neck to an enemy.

51:17.353 --> 51:19.053
God damn it.

51:19.055 --> 51:21.522
The S.E.C. may be feckless,
but they're not incompetent.

51:21.557 --> 51:22.806
Where's the stock at?

51:22.858 --> 51:24.641
Oh, they just made an announcement.

51:24.693 --> 51:25.726
It's cascading down.

51:25.728 --> 51:26.894
It is time to dump out.

51:26.896 --> 51:28.896
Hold it.

51:28.898 --> 51:30.898
- Come on.
- You'll hold it.

51:30.950 --> 51:33.067
No profit.

51:33.119 --> 51:34.568
Nothing to entice a prosecutor,

51:34.570 --> 51:38.005
nothing fancy or flashy to sell a jury.

51:38.040 --> 51:40.157
The great Charles Rhoades
won't be winning this one

51:40.209 --> 51:41.742
and dazzling the Street once again.

51:41.794 --> 51:43.961
Don't you get it? Don't you understand?

51:43.996 --> 51:46.797
This wasn't about me
making a few shekels.

51:46.832 --> 51:49.750
This was about me striking
at our common enemy,

51:49.802 --> 51:51.585
to hurt him where he lives.

51:51.587 --> 51:52.586
I do understand.

51:52.638 --> 51:53.921
You want me to get Axe

51:53.923 --> 51:56.173
because he fucked with your side piece

51:56.225 --> 51:57.925
and then he beat you.

51:57.977 --> 52:03.414
[Chuck Sr.] For both of us! And I
did it because you wouldn't act.

52:04.967 --> 52:06.400
[computer beeps]

52:06.435 --> 52:08.268
Oh, Christ.

52:08.320 --> 52:09.686
It's at $65.

52:09.738 --> 52:11.321
At least let me take a small piece.

52:11.357 --> 52:13.273
Not even a fucking taste.

52:15.811 --> 52:18.178
Okay.

52:18.214 --> 52:20.414
You've made your point, son. I get it.

52:20.449 --> 52:21.448
It's not a game.

52:21.450 --> 52:23.083
I shouldn't have gone
off-piste like this.

52:23.119 --> 52:26.620
But by the time I get
out, with commissions,

52:26.622 --> 52:28.188
- I'll be lucky to break even.
- No.

52:30.960 --> 52:32.126
[computer beeps]

52:32.178 --> 52:34.595
$55. This is where I bought in.

52:34.630 --> 52:37.326
It's not a crime anymore.
It's a sell-off.

52:38.601 --> 52:41.018
A little more medicine.

52:41.053 --> 52:44.171
This is goddamn ridiculous.

52:50.179 --> 52:51.845
[Chuck Sr.] It's below $45.

52:55.818 --> 52:59.319
[dialing]

52:59.371 --> 53:02.256
[ringing]

53:02.291 --> 53:04.625
Clark, get me out of CXC.

53:04.660 --> 53:06.560
All of it.

53:11.917 --> 53:14.334
I just dumped $480,000 on this.

53:14.370 --> 53:16.086
[scoffs]

53:16.138 --> 53:17.638
Axelrod still made

53:17.673 --> 53:21.475
at least $15 million, despite it all.

53:23.395 --> 53:25.345
Are you happy now?

53:26.982 --> 53:29.683
Do I look fucking happy?

53:31.320 --> 53:33.187
[sighs]

53:33.189 --> 53:36.607
Will you get this son of a bitch already?

53:38.577 --> 53:40.527
[indistinct conversations]

53:40.579 --> 53:43.197
♪<i> mid-tempo music plays</i> ♪

53:45.301 --> 53:48.168
I've got a good one to show you, boss.

53:48.204 --> 53:49.786
Hey. Good trip?

53:49.838 --> 53:52.539
Whatever you did to Garth Sykes
gentled him down real good.

53:52.591 --> 53:54.541
He e-mailed, said he's
ready to soar with you,

53:54.593 --> 53:55.959
whatever the fuck that means.

53:58.214 --> 53:59.813
[Sighs]

53:59.848 --> 54:01.848
[indistinct conversations]

54:04.303 --> 54:07.454
Sorry. Sorry.

54:19.034 --> 54:22.135
[Bobby] Eat. Move.

54:22.171 --> 54:25.989
Shit. Repeat.

54:26.041 --> 54:27.624
[Wags] What?

54:27.660 --> 54:29.309
Sell everything.

54:31.046 --> 54:32.846
Everything?

54:32.881 --> 54:34.047
[chuckling] What the fuck happened to you

54:34.083 --> 54:35.048
while you were gone?

54:35.084 --> 54:37.417
5% from all our positions

54:37.453 --> 54:39.386
right across the board, for starters.

54:39.421 --> 54:41.901
De-lever. But take it slow.

54:41.926 --> 54:43.492
Control the bleeding.

54:44.760 --> 54:46.009
Then we'll dump, sector by sector,

54:46.061 --> 54:48.028
starting with telecom.

54:48.063 --> 54:50.397
[Andrew Bird's "Oh No" plays]

54:50.432 --> 54:52.399
- People will think...
- That I'm out.

54:56.355 --> 54:57.904
So, are you?

